	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: New in Nes development</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Definitely get the cc65 package and start with that. It contains a very powerful macro assembler (ca65) that compiles to object files, and has a linker (ld65). The package also contains a C compiler that you can start using once you get your feet wet.<br /><br />Shiru's article linked above is an excellent starting point if you already know C.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


